    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1879-08-05T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1879-08-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="434" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d434">
                <head>No. 403.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Christianey</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Evarts</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of
                                    the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Lima,
                                Peru</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1879-08-05">
                            <hi rend="italic">August</hi> 5, 1879</date>. (Received
                            September 4.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 46.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to inform you that President
                        Prado telegraphs from Iquique that the Chilian fleet has voluntarily raised
                        the blockade of that port, and by a subsequent dispatch he says they are at
                        present in Autafogasta.</p>
                <p>I have, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>I. P. CHRISTIANCY.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
